King, Stephen (1982) ‘The Dark Tower: the Gunslinger’, artist signed first edition + King signature – First and Fine – Rare and Collectable Books



































 
















 


King, Stephen (1982) ‘The Dark Tower: the Gunslinger’, artist signed first edition + King signature£1,200.00

Stephen King (1982) ‘The Gunslinger’, US first edition signed by illustrator Michael Whelan on the title page. In addition Stephen King’s signature loosely inserted on a First Day Cover with an Elvis stamp. Published by Grant. This is the first book of King’s eight volumes strong ‘Dark Tower’ series.

Condition: like new. The book is very fine with no flaws whatsoever. The dust jacket is in near fine condition with slight fading to the spine and with the tiniest of creasing to the folds only. The book is housed in an aftermarket custom made slipcase.


In stock




Add to basket


Category: Fantasy





Description


Additional information


Reviews (0)



Description
No other contemporary writer has influenced popular culture as much as the ‘King of Horror’, Stephen King. With a staggering output of short stories, novellas and novels Hollywood has been eager to adapt many of his ideas and books.
The Dark Tower is meant to be Stephen King’s ‘Lord of the Rings’ style magnum opus. It was initially published in five instalments in The Magazine of Fantasy and Science Fiction between 1978 and 1981. This is the first trade hardback copy, and King and the publisher anticipated slow sales only due to the fantasy nature of the story rather than his usual horror appeal. That is why the print run was only 10,000 copies  of which about 1,500 copies were misbound. as a comparison ‘The Shining’, and his debut novel ‘Carrie’ had a prin run of 25,000 and 30,000 respectively.
For July 2017, a movie adaptation has been announced titled ‘The Dark Tower’ starring Idris Alba and Matthew David McConaughey. This will surely boost once more interest in the already popular Dark Tower series.
A highly collectible book especially in such great condition. Michael Whelan’s King’s signature is a bonus!


Additional information


