There was a problem loading comments right now. Please try again later.4.0 out of 5 starsThe ending legitimately made me angry.ByVéronique Bellamyon March 12, 2017Format: Mass Market Paperback|Verified PurchaseWarning: there are spoilers ahead. If you want to avoid them, read just my first paragraph and the title.I love the Dark Tower series. I read through all seven books and I'm rereading the series now (and doing it with Wind through the Keyhole in its proper place between books 4 & 5). It was a book and a series that kept me riveted.... Though the ending pissed me off. I understand that there probably was no way King could have ended the story. The Dark Tower was built up so much throughout the series that it would have taken something spectacular to live up to it... Really, anything would have been a letdown. The ending was cheap, but as far as letdowns go, this made me angry. Legitimately angry.But how else was it supposed to end? Life isn't always accompanied by a happy ending. Life isn't always a field of roses. I think, too often, we don't appreciate this and instead prefer to have sunshine blown up our butts 24/7. The ending is sad, it's gritty and while there is hope, one can't finish the book without saying, "WTF, King?"0Comment|
